children.subject: The North American Qualifier (http://cs.baylor.edu/~hamerly/icpc/qualifier_2019/) seems to be five hours rather than three. Will we be taking the contest with a shorter time limit?
Are we competing in the North American Qualifier in teams of 3 or 1?
Unspecified.  The qualifier outcome gives us an idea of the top programmers, but putting them together into well-integrated teams may take a bit of work.
How does selection work after the qualifier? Do you have to get a certain score on it to qualify or be in the top x% of people? Or is it just used to make the teams?
Interpret 1996-1998 as up to but not including 1998.
Does it matter what I select for year I was born since there are two options for 1998?
Strictly individually.  You won't be able to just register a team of your own choosing in the regional contest in any case.
If we have a team already, can we compete as a team or strictly individual?
Depends on (1) the demand from other schools, (2) the number of people who do well enough in the NAQ contest.

Opportunistically asking, what would be the expected number of teams to be selected for ICPC regionals?
Last year it was Berkeley Blue/Gold/Radicals which is a total of 3 teams competing in Div 1. Would this year be something similar?
Virtually.  With 107 participants, it would be difficult to find a suitable location.
Will the contest be done virtually or at a location on campus?
'Fraid not.  There is, however, an open contest, described in http://cs.baylor.edu/~hamerly/icpc/qualifier_2019/
Can we no longer sign up to participate?

history.content:
You can now sign up for the Berkeley Programming Contest using this link

This year, we will again be using the North American Qualifier (NAQ) Contest to help us form teams for the ACM Northwest Pacific Regional Programming Contest. Even though many people continent-wide will be competing, we're actually only going to use the results for Berkeley students who sign up here. The NAQ will take place online on October 5, 2019, at 11:00 - 16:00 (PDT). After the NAQ, we'll be organizing teams of 3 for the Regional Contest, which will take place on November 9th at an as-yet undisclosed location.

Our contest is limited to current Berkeley students who can attend the regional contest.
